{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":613,"text":"So why do we learn mathematics?"},{"time":3652,"text":"Essentially, for three reasons:"},{"time":6200,"text":"calculation,"},{"time":7828,"text":"application,"},{"time":9728,"text":"and last, and unfortunately least"},{"time":12415,"text":"in terms of the time we give it,"},{"time":14520,"text":"inspiration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16442,"text":"Mathematics is the science of patterns,"},{"time":18714,"text":"and we study it to learn how to think logically,"},{"time":22072,"text":"critically and creatively,"},{"time":24599,"text":"but too much of the mathematics\nthat we learn in school"},{"time":27525,"text":"is not effectively motivated,"},{"time":29844,"text":"and when our students ask,"},{"time":31269,"text":"\"Why are we learning this?\""},{"time":32944,"text":"then they often hear that they'll need it"},{"time":34905,"text":"in an upcoming math class or on a future test."},{"time":38170,"text":"But wouldn't it be great"},{"time":39972,"text":"if every once in a while we did mathematics"},{"time":42490,"text":"simply because it was fun or beautiful"},{"time":45439,"text":"or because it excited the mind?"},{"time":47529,"text":"Now, I know many people have not"},{"time":49251,"text":"had the opportunity to see how this can happen,"},{"time":51570,"text":"so let me give you a quick example"},{"time":53399,"text":"with my favorite collection of numbers,"},{"time":55740,"text":"the Fibonacci numbers. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58468,"text":"Yeah! I already have Fibonacci fans here."},{"time":60520,"text":"That's great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61836,"text":"Now these numbers can be appreciated"},{"time":63952,"text":"in many different ways."},{"time":65830,"text":"From the standpoint of calculation,"},{"time":68539,"text":"they're as easy to understand"},{"time":70216,"text":"as one plus one, which is two."},{"time":72770,"text":"Then one plus two is three,"},{"time":74773,"text":"two plus three is five, three plus five is eight,"},{"time":77787,"text":"and so on."},{"time":79312,"text":"Indeed, the person we call Fibonacci"},{"time":81489,"text":"was actually named Leonardo of Pisa,"},{"time":84669,"text":"and these numbers appear in his book \"Liber Abaci,\""},{"time":87722,"text":"which taught the Western world"},{"time":89372,"text":"the methods of arithmetic that we use today."},{"time":92199,"text":"In terms of applications,"},{"time":93920,"text":"Fibonacci numbers appear in nature"},{"time":96103,"text":"surprisingly often."},{"time":97960,"text":"The number of petals on a flower"},{"time":99700,"text":"is typically a Fibonacci number,"},{"time":101562,"text":"or the number of spirals on a sunflower"},{"time":104332,"text":"or a pineapple"},{"time":105743,"text":"tends to be a Fibonacci number as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108137,"text":"In fact, there are many more\napplications of Fibonacci numbers,"},{"time":111640,"text":"but what I find most inspirational about them"},{"time":114200,"text":"are the beautiful number patterns they display."},{"time":116934,"text":"Let me show you one of my favorites."},{"time":119128,"text":"Suppose you like to square numbers,"},{"time":121349,"text":"and frankly, who doesn't? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":124040,"text":"Let's look at the squares"},{"time":126280,"text":"of the first few Fibonacci numbers."},{"time":128131,"text":"So one squared is one,"},{"time":130161,"text":"two squared is four, three squared is nine,"},{"time":132478,"text":"five squared is 25, and so on."},{"time":135651,"text":"Now, it's no surprise"},{"time":137552,"text":"that when you add consecutive Fibonacci numbers,"},{"time":140380,"text":"you get the next Fibonacci number. Right?"},{"time":142412,"text":"That's how they're created."},{"time":143807,"text":"But you wouldn't expect anything special"},{"time":145580,"text":"to happen when you add the squares together."},{"time":148656,"text":"But check this out."},{"time":150002,"text":"One plus one gives us two,"},{"time":152003,"text":"and one plus four gives us five."},{"time":154765,"text":"And four plus nine is 13,"},{"time":156960,"text":"nine plus 25 is 34,"},{"time":160173,"text":"and yes, the pattern continues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162832,"text":"In fact, here's another one."},{"time":164453,"text":"Suppose you wanted to look at"},{"time":166297,"text":"adding the squares of\nthe first few Fibonacci numbers."},{"time":168795,"text":"Let's see what we get there."},{"time":170403,"text":"So one plus one plus four is six."},{"time":172542,"text":"Add nine to that, we get 15."},{"time":175547,"text":"Add 25, we get 40."},{"time":177760,"text":"Add 64, we get 104."},{"time":180551,"text":"Now look at those numbers."},{"time":182203,"text":"Those are not Fibonacci numbers,"},{"time":184587,"text":"but if you look at them closely,"},{"time":186466,"text":"you'll see the Fibonacci numbers"},{"time":188349,"text":"buried inside of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190527,"text":"Do you see it? I'll show it to you."},{"time":192597,"text":"Six is two times three, 15 is three times five,"},{"time":196330,"text":"40 is five times eight,"},{"time":198389,"text":"two, three, five, eight, who do we appreciate?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201317,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202504,"text":"Fibonacci! Of course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204659,"text":"Now, as much fun as it is to discover these patterns,"},{"time":208442,"text":"it's even more satisfying to understand"},{"time":210924,"text":"why they are true."},{"time":212882,"text":"Let's look at that last equation."},{"time":214771,"text":"Why should the squares of one, one,\ntwo, three, five and eight"},{"time":218639,"text":"add up to eight times 13?"},{"time":221184,"text":"I'll show you by drawing a simple picture."},{"time":224145,"text":"We'll start with a one-by-one square"},{"time":226832,"text":"and next to that put another one-by-one square."},{"time":230997,"text":"Together, they form a one-by-two rectangle."},{"time":234405,"text":"Beneath that, I'll put a two-by-two square,"},{"time":236954,"text":"and next to that, a three-by-three square,"},{"time":239749,"text":"beneath that, a five-by-five square,"},{"time":241750,"text":"and then an eight-by-eight square,"},{"time":243662,"text":"creating one giant rectangle, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246234,"text":"Now let me ask you a simple question:"},{"time":248150,"text":"what is the area of the rectangle?"},{"time":251806,"text":"Well, on the one hand,"},{"time":253777,"text":"it's the sum of the areas"},{"time":256307,"text":"of the squares inside it, right?"},{"time":258173,"text":"Just as we created it."},{"time":259532,"text":"It's one squared plus one squared"},{"time":261704,"text":"plus two squared plus three squared"},{"time":263937,"text":"plus five squared plus eight squared. Right?"},{"time":266536,"text":"That's the area."},{"time":268393,"text":"On the other hand, because it's a rectangle,"},{"time":270719,"text":"the area is equal to its height times its base,"},{"time":274367,"text":"and the height is clearly eight,"},{"time":276414,"text":"and the base is five plus eight,"},{"time":279317,"text":"which is the next Fibonacci number, 13. Right?"},{"time":283255,"text":"So the area is also eight times 13."},{"time":286618,"text":"Since we've correctly calculated the area"},{"time":288880,"text":"two different ways,"},{"time":290567,"text":"they have to be the same number,"},{"time":292739,"text":"and that's why the squares of one,\none, two, three, five and eight"},{"time":296130,"text":"add up to eight times 13."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298421,"text":"Now, if we continue this process,"},{"time":300795,"text":"we'll generate rectangles of the form 13 by 21,"},{"time":304773,"text":"21 by 34, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307167,"text":"Now check this out."},{"time":308576,"text":"If you divide 13 by eight,"},{"time":310769,"text":"you get 1.625."},{"time":312812,"text":"And if you divide the larger number\nby the smaller number,"},{"time":316239,"text":"then these ratios get closer and closer"},{"time":319112,"text":"to about 1.618,"},{"time":321765,"text":"known to many people as the Golden Ratio,"},{"time":325066,"text":"a number which has fascinated mathematicians,"},{"time":327662,"text":"scientists and artists for centuries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330908,"text":"Now, I show all this to you because,"},{"time":333139,"text":"like so much of mathematics,"},{"time":335164,"text":"there's a beautiful side to it"},{"time":337131,"text":"that I fear does not get enough attention"},{"time":339146,"text":"in our schools."},{"time":340713,"text":"We spend lots of time learning about calculation,"},{"time":343546,"text":"but let's not forget about application,"},{"time":346302,"text":"including, perhaps, the most\nimportant application of all,"},{"time":349756,"text":"learning how to think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351832,"text":"If I could summarize this in one sentence,"},{"time":353789,"text":"it would be this:"},{"time":355250,"text":"Mathematics is not just solving for x,"},{"time":358610,"text":"it's also figuring out why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361535,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363350,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}